This Privacy Policy does not apply to information submitted or collected through websites maintained by other companies or organizations to which we may link or who may link to us. We are not responsible for the actions and privacy policies of third-party websites.
Additionally, if you use a Klarna/WebBank product, your non-public personal information will be subject to
WebBank’s privacy notice
and Klarna’s use of such information will be consistent with that privacy notice.
1. What type of information does Klarna collect?
We collect two basic types of information from you in conjunction with your use of the Klarna Services (collectively, your “personal information”): (1) personally identifiable information; and (2) non-personally identifiable information.
Personally Identifiable Information
is any information that can identify you.
Examples include your name, e-mail address, telephone number, postal address, device identifiers, IP addresses, geolocation information, and financial account information that you provide, such as credit or debit card numbers.
We may also collect personally identifiable information about you from third parties such as data vendors.
Aggregate and/or de-identified information is not considered personally identifiable information.
Non-personally identifiable information
is information that does not identify you directly, but may be linkable to you.
Examples include demographic information and general location information.
If non-personally identifiable information is directly linked to personally identifiable information, it will be considered personally identifiable information while it is linked. For example, if your payment history and transaction history are linked to your name, then that information will be considered personally identifiable information and subject to heightened privacy and security restrictions, as reflected in this Privacy Policy.
2. How does Klarna Collect Information?
We collect information about you through:
Your interactions with or use of the Klarna Services, including both information you give us, as well as information we derive from your usage;
Your contact with our customer support and other communications with us;
Third parties, such as data vendors, consumer reporting agencies, your bank, payment service providers you use, or merchants you perform a transaction with;
Through our websites and mobile applications, using cookies, Clear GIFs, web beacons, mobile application plug-ins, browser extension and similar technologies.
Cookies
are small files that are stored on your computer or device when you use the Klarna Services. Cookies record your preferences and the actions you take on your computer or device. We may also use web beacons and mobile application plug-ins, such as software development kits, application programming interfaces and similar technologies. We use these and other similar technologies for security, to monitor traffic, improve the Klarna Services, and make the Klarna Services easier to use and more relevant to you. We may also use these technologies to personalize your experience, deliver advertisements, and for research and marketing.
You can learn more about ad-serving companies and the options available to limit their collection and use of your information by visiting the websites for the Network Advertising Initiative and the Digital Advertising Alliance. Similarly, you can learn about your options to opt out of mobile app tracking by certain advertising networks through your device settings and by resetting the advertiser ID on your Apple or Android device.
Clear GIFs
are tiny graphics with a unique identifier, similar in function to cookies. In contrast to cookies, which are stored on your computer’s hard drive, clear GIFs are embedded invisibly on web pages. We may use clear GIFs (a.k.a. web beacons, web bugs or pixel tags), in connection with the Klarna Services to, among other things, track the activities of Site visitors, help us manage content, and compile statistics about usage of Klarna Services.
Third Party Analytics
We may use automated devices and applications provided by third parties to evaluate usage of the Klarna Services. We use these tools to help us improve the Klarna Services, performance and user experiences. These entities may use cookies and other tracking technologies to perform their services.
Sometimes when you communicate with us, or utilize our services we use third party service providers. In some cases these service providers may monitor and record mouse movements, swiping, scrolling, clicks, and keystrokes so that we can better understand how our products are utilized, and in some cases they may provide interfaces that allow you to communicate with us, for example through a chat window. In these cases, we maintain contracts with these third parties and they are required to keep your information confidential. By utilizing the Klarna Services you consent to our use of service providers for these purposes.
3. How do we use the personal information we collect?
We may use your personal information to:
Provide the Klarna Services and customer support.
Process transactions and send notices about your transactions.
Resolve disputes and collect payments and/or fees.
Verify the accuracy of and authenticate your information.
Detect, investigate and prevent potentially prohibited or illegal activities, such as fraud.
Communicate about accounts or transactions and send information about features and enhancements.
Contact you, for example by phone, text (SMS) or email.
Communicate changes to our policies.
Personalize content and experiences, including providing recommendations based on your preferences and queries.
Publish product and merchant reviews that you submit.
Send offers or promotions for the Klarna Services.
Provide advertising, including advertising based on your use of the Klarna Services or third-party websites.
Improve and develop Klarna Services and new products and services.
Perform statistical, demographic and marketing analyses of users of the Klarna Services and their purchasing patterns.
Conduct any other legitimate business activities not otherwise prohibited by law.
4. How do we share personal information?
We will only share your personal information with third parties as described in this Privacy Policy. When we share your personal information we include reasonable contractual, legal, technical and organizational measures to ensure that your information is processed with an adequate level of protection and in accordance with applicable law.
We may share your personal information with:
Service providers, affiliates and commercial partners who help with our business operations including but not limited to, fraud prevention, account maintenance, customer service, marketing and technology services.
Consumer reporting agencies, fraud detection companies and collection agencies, as permitted by law.
Merchants you order goods or services from using the Klarna Services.
Marketing or advertising partners who assist us in serving advertising. These partners may use tracking technologies to collect or receive information through the Klarna Services and elsewhere on the internet and use that information to provide measurement services and targeted ads. These marketing or advertising partners may allow third party companies to access information about you so that those companies may market other products you may be interested in.
Analytics companies.
Companies that we plan to merge with or be acquired by or to whom we may sell or transfer our assets, including as part of a reorganization or bankruptcy proceeding.
Third parties, including governmental authorities and law enforcement, to (i) protect or defend the legal rights, interests or property of Klarna and any related entity of Klarna; (ii) protect the safety and security of our customers or members of the public; (iii) protect against fraud; or (iv) comply with applicable law, or with a civil, criminal, or regulatory inquiry, investigation, subpoena, or summons. Including, without limitation, LexisNexis Risk Solutions Group; Emailage and ThreatMetrix services:
Processing Notices | LexisNexis Risk Solutions
.
Other third parties with your consent or at your direction to do so.
Third parties for any legitimate business purpose not otherwise prohibited by law.
We will only share your Personal Information with third parties as described in this Privacy Policy, as otherwise notified to you at the time of collection (for example as set forth in an agreement you have entered into with us) or with your consent.
Text messaging originator opt-in data and consent will not be shared with any of the third parties listed in this section except, as stated as below for the purpose of providing the
Klarna Marketing Text Message Program
to consumers.
5. Product Specific Information
The following information relates to specific products offered by Klarna.
5.1 Auto-Track (available in the Klarna App)
The Auto-Track feature (previously Magic Import) is described in
these terms and conditions
. If you connect to the Auto-Track feature, we will process order information (such as delivery tracking identifiers, supplier information, product information, and payment information) related to purchases you have made, and email information (to identify the relevant order and delivery information), in order to provide you with delivery information and an overview of your purchases in the Klarna App. We may also identify any relevant promotional codes to present to you in the Klarna App.
Data obtained through the service is shared with our service provider in order to provide the service to you. Neither Klarna nor our service provider will share data obtained through Auto-Track with any third parties, unless necessary to provide or improve the service to you. We will not transfer data to third parties for serving ads.
5.2 Klarna Desktop Extension
Klarna Desktop Extension is a browser extension of the Klarna Services available for select web browsers. By downloading and using the Klarna Desktop Extension you can request and use One-time Cards directly in your browser on websites where this service is enabled in accordance with our internal policies. When you browse the internet with the Klarna Desktop Extension enabled, we will receive the domain of the websites that you visit. To the extent this is personal information, it will be handled in compliance with the terms of this Privacy Policy.
5.3 Sponsored Links
If you click on a link that is sponsored which promotes a store, product or service you will be redirected to the store’s website through a third party, a so-called “affiliate network.” The affiliate network might place a tracking technology on your device that contains the information that you clicked on such a link in the Klarna App, which then may be used to track your visit to a store in order to calculate a potential commission to us.
5.4 Google
When you use Google Maps in the checkout (for example by searching for your address in the address field) or the Klarna App, Google will process your information subject to Google Maps’/Google Earth's
Terms of Service
and
Privacy Policy
.
5.5 Rakuten
We partner with Rakuten Advertising, who may collect personal information when you interact with the Klarna Services. The collection and use of this information is subject to the privacy policy located here:
Rakuten’s privacy policy;
To submit an opt-out request
5.6 Klarna Marketing Text Message Program
If you opt-in to
Klarna’s Marketing Text Message Program
, we will not share any information collected through your opt-in to the program or through our marketing text message short code with any third parties. The information collected through these activities will only be used to collect and store a record of your consent and to send SMS messages, and keep a record of such communications, to the mobile number on record for the purposes of the Klarna Marketing Text Message Program.
5.7 Identification and Verification Process
In this section we explain how we collect, use and disclose your biometric data for identification and verification purposes in line with U.S. state biometric privacy laws such as the Illinois Biometric Information Privacy Act, the Texas Act on Capture or Use of Biometric Identifier, or the Washington Biometric Privacy Law (H.B. 1493).
In order to verify that you are the person depicted in your government-issued identification document, Klarna uses third-party technologies from the following identification and verification vendors (“ID&V Vendors”) to collect personal information from or about you, including biometric information and biometric identifiers such as your faceprint (“Biometric Information”), a selfie, and government-issued identification, including information contained within the barcode (collectively the “ID&V Personal Information”):
