page.
14.3.5 Categories of Personal Information Disclosed
In the preceding 12 months, we have disclosed personal information for a business or commercial purpose, as permitted or required by law or as otherwise set forth in this Policy. When we disclose personal information to a service provider, we enter into a contract that describes our business purpose for disclosing and requires the service provider to keep personal information confidential and to use it only for purposes consistent with the contract between us.
We may disclose all categories of your personal information for a business or commercial purpose to the following third parties:
Service providers, affiliates and commercial partners who help with our business operations, including but not limited to, fraud prevention, account maintenance, customer service, marketing and technology services.
Consumer reporting agencies, fraud detection companies and collection agencies, as permitted by law.
Merchants you order goods or services from using the Klarna Services.
Marketing or advertising partners who assist us in serving advertising. These partners may use tracking technologies to collect or receive information through the Klarna Services and elsewhere on the internet and use that information to provide measurement services and targeted ads. These marketing or advertising partners may allow third party companies to access information about you so that those companies may market other products you may be interested in.
Analytics companies.
Companies that we plan to merge with or be acquired by or to whom we may sell or transfer our assets, including as part of a reorganization or bankruptcy proceeding.
